display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a topological space.
    Then a <fr:em>cohomological Hodge <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex></fr:em> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> consists of:

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(𝛼) &quot;">
        a complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_A\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+(X,A)]]></fr:tex>,
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(𝛽) &quot;">
        a filtered complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+F(X,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>,
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(𝛾) &quot;">
        an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  K_\mathbb {C}\simeq  K_A\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(X,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p><fr:p>The following axiom has to be satisfied:

    <fr:tree
